# Build toolchain — the PEP-517 build frontend (`build`) plus the
# backend requires (`setuptools`, `wheel`) used to produce sdists and
# wheels. Hash-pinned via `requirements-build.txt` so that:
#   - ci.yml's `pip install -e . --no-deps --no-build-isolation` uses a
#     hash-verified host setuptools/wheel instead of fetching the
#     PEP-517 build-system requires from PyPI unpinned (addresses #162).
#   - release.yml's `python -m build --no-isolation` builds and signs
#     artifacts with a hash-verified toolchain instead of an unpinned
#     `build` frontend + an isolated, unpinned backend fetch (addresses
#     #168, and the release-side backend gap neither issue scoped).
#
# Regenerate (Python 3.11, pip-tools 7.5.3 — same toolchain as
# requirements-dev.txt; see CLAUDE.md):
#   pip-compile --generate-hashes --no-strip-extras --allow-unsafe -o requirements-build.txt requirements-build.in
#
# `--allow-unsafe` is REQUIRED here (unlike the dev lockfile): pip-tools
# classifies setuptools/wheel as "unsafe to pin" and comments them out
# by default, which would defeat --no-build-isolation. `--no-strip-extras`
# mirrors the dev lockfile so a future pip-tools 8.0 default flip cannot
# silently prune transitive extras. -c below constrains shared transitive
# deps (e.g. packaging) to the versions already pinned in
# requirements-dev.txt so ci.yml can install both lockfiles without skew.
-c requirements-dev.txt

build
# Floor mirrors pyproject.toml [build-system].requires; the resolved
# version is pinned in requirements-build.txt.
setuptools>=68
wheel
